{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Reaction Diffusion",
  "description": "Gray-Scott reaction-diffusion: two virtual chemicals feed, react, and diffuse, growing coral, fingerprint, and labyrinth patterns from a seeded dish. The update kernel is the classic Gray-Scott step (Sims 9-point weighted Laplacian, Du=1.0/Dv=0.5, fp32 field, U in the red channel, V in green) run four substeps per frame as chained JSON-editable WGSL nodes \u2014 the DECOMPOSING_GENERATORS \u00a75 sanctioned escape-hatch case for a domain-specific coupled kernel. The dish state lives in one feedback node seeded with U=1 everywhere and a V blob in the centre; clip triggers stamp fresh V at the Inject point through an attack/release envelope. Feed and Kill are the regime plane \u2014 sweeping them tours spots, stripes, and waves live (coral f=0.055/k=0.062 (default), waves f=0.014/k=0.045, mitosis around f=0.037/k=0.065). Develop extracts the V field, shapes it with levels, and grades through a gradient LUT on pure black.",
